The paper is focused on modelling and metamodelling in software engineering, which is a core area of computer science. The paper specifically discusses instance generation techniques for metamodels, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses machine learning techniques for generating instances, which could fall under the sub-categories of programming languages (cs.PL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of instance generation in system engineering (cs.SY).
